We are delighted to share with you our Unravelled Descent quilt, designed by And Objects as part of @christopherfarrcloth’s upcoming exhibition ’Threads of Life’.
 
Representing the distinct design dialogue that And Objects shares with Christopher Farr Cloth, we have crafted a quilt that tells a story of remarkable craftsmanship and celebrates rich textile traditions.
 
Taking place at @nantucketbydesign, ‘Threads of Life’ will be on from August 2nd to August 5th, with all proceeds of the sales of the quilts going to support the Nantucket Historical Association.

Interior designer Martin Brudnizki (@martinbrudnizki) and his art consultant partner Jonathan Brook (@jonathan_brook) like to let their imaginations run riot at home in West Sussex, especially at this time of year. Part of a large 17th-century house in West Sussex, their flat, with its grand proportions and ornate original features, provides the perfect backdrop for indulging their lavish, country-house decorating dreams. Follow the link in our profile to tour their 17th-century Sussex flat in full .
